28/03/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- A local NGO, the Coalition for Women and Youth Participation in Politics, urged women Monday (27 March) to participate more in domestic politics and decision-making processes.
The organisation issued a statement noting that while women make up 51 per cent of the country's population, there are only ten women in parliament and none in senior positions in municipal administrations.
In other news, Albanian Prime Minister Sali Berisha visited Prague on Monday.
Czech counterpart Jiri Paroubek and President Vaclav Klaus assured him of their country's full support for Albania's EU aspirations.
(Albanian News - 28/03/06;
RFE - 27/03/06)
